The application shall contain:
The full name and Maryland address of the owner, including:
If the owner is an individual, the owner's Maryland residence and mailing addresses;
If the owner is a business firm, association, or corporation, its federal identification number and:
Its business address in this State; or
The name and address of its resident agent in this State;
If the owner is a partnership or joint venture, the name of each partner or joint venturer;
If the owner is an unincorporated association, joint stock company, or other group described in § 6-406 of the Courts Article, the name and address of a resident agent on whom service may be made in any lawsuit arising out of the ownership, maintenance, or use of the vehicle; and
If the owner is a trustee, the address of the trust in this State and the name and address of a person in this State on whom service may be made in any lawsuit arising out of the ownership, maintenance, or use of the vehicle;
If the owner is an individual, the owner's date of birth; and
If the owner is a partnership or joint venture, the date of birth of each partner or joint venturer;
A description of the vehicle, including:
To the extent that the information exists, its make, model, year, vehicle identification number, type of body, and number of cylinders;
If the vehicle is a two-stage vehicle:
The make and year of the first stage; and
The make, model, and year of the second stage;
If the vehicle is a motorcycle with an engine manufactured on or after January 1, 1977, the identifying number of the engine; and
Any other information that the Administration requires;
A statement of:
The applicant's title to and each security interest in the vehicle; and
The name and address of each secured party with any security interest in the vehicle and the nature and order of priority of that interest; and
Any other information that the Administration reasonably requires to determine if the owner is entitled to a certificate of title.

The application shall be signed in ink by:
Each owner who is an individual;
The individual cosigning the application on behalf of a minor in accordance with subsection (b) of this section;
An officer or authorized agent of the owner, if the owner is a business firm, association, or corporation;
A partner or joint venturer, if the owner is a partnership or joint venture;
An officer or authorized agent, if the owner is an unincorporated association, joint stock company, or other group described in § 6-406 of the Courts Article; or
A trustee, if the owner is a trust.
